        "body": "**Describe the bug**\nThe documentation shows DEL → Delete selected element, but the shortcut does not work anywhere in the editor (tables, notes, areas, relationships).\nThis suggests the feature is documented but not implemented.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Create any element\n2. Select it\n3. Press Delete\n4. Nothing happens\n\n**Expected behavior**\nPressing Delete removes the selected element as documented.\n\n**Screenshots**\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a5bd4dc9-e257-459b-b99c-13f29ab42c2b)\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c914ea71-4e56-4946-a3b3-5bc3ac7841f0\n\nI’ve attached:\n\n📸 Screenshot from the official shortcut list\n\n🎥 Screen recording showing that pressing Delete has no effect\n\nDesktop:\nOS: macOS\nBrowser: Google Chrome (latest)\nReproducible: Yes (both normal and incognito mode)\n",
